{"questionId":"27917","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The time of sunrise, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>R</mi></math> hours after midnight, in Taipei can be modelled by</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>R</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>08</mn><mo> </mo><mi>cos</mi><mfenced><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>0165</mn><mi>t</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>413</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>+</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>94</mn></math>,</p>\n<p>where <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>t</mi></math> is the day of the year <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2021</mn></math> (for example, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>t</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn></math> represents 2 January 2021).</p>\n<p>The time of sunset, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>S</mi></math> hours after midnight, in Taipei can be modelled by</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>S</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>15</mn><mo> </mo><mi>cos</mi><mfenced><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>0165</mn><mi>t</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>97</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>+</mo><mn>18</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>9</mn></math>.</p>\n<p>The number of daylight hours, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>D</mi></math>, in Taipei during 2021 can be modelled by</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>D</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>a</mi><mo> </mo><mi>cos</mi><mfenced><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>0165</mn><mi>t</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>b</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>+</mo><mi>c</mi></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Hence, or otherwise, find the largest number of daylight hours in Taipei during <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2021</mn></math>&nbsp;and the day of the year on which this occurs.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>16</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>16</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>1737</mn><mo>…</mo></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp;hours on day&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>173</mn></math>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><br><strong>Note:</strong> Accept an answer of “day <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>172</mn></math>” for the second <em><strong>A1</strong></em>.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"27917","referenceCode":"22N.1.AHL.TZ0.17b","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Hence, or otherwise, find the largest number of daylight hours in Taipei during 2021 and the day of the year on which this occurs.","paper":"1","level":"HL","questionNumber":"b","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 1—Number and algebra","Topic 1—Number and algebra","AHL 1.13—Polar and Euler form"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}